## rustc workspace wrapper script generation

DESIGN Q4 part 3: `RUSTC_WORKSPACE_WRAPPER` is a thin shell around
rustc that inspects `CARGO_CFG_*` env vars and computes flag sets
from the three axes (Target, Tier, Passes). The skeleton ships the
Rust-side type surface; the bash / PowerShell script emitter lands
in a follow-up round after the pragma types are battle-tested
against a concrete consumer.

## LLVM pass plugin C++ source

DESIGN describes a ~40-line C++ LLVM plugin with two extension
points: `VectorizerStartEP` (IRCE, LoopPredication, SimplifyCFG,
LoopInterchange, LoopDistribute) and `OptimizerLastEP`
(LoopDataPrefetch, SeparateConstOffsetFromGEP, LoopFusion
conditional). Delivery: a pre-built dylib per target triple
shipped alongside the toolchain. Lands in its own round with
build-system (CMake) + distribution story.

## PGO / BOLT tier integration

DESIGN Q5 tiers:
- Static BOLT (3-5% gain).
- PGO (10-20% branch / inline).
- Profile-guided BOLT on PGO (additional 5-10%).
Each tier is an independent round with its own profraw collection,
sample-conversion tooling, and CI integration. Profile staleness
warning (>50 commits diverged) ships with the PGO round.

## hilavitkutin-config.toml schema

Skeleton writes a placeholder file. Real schema serialises the
resolved `PragmaSet` for downstream tools (e.g. ide-helper,
build-introspection). Follow-up round pins the TOML shape and
adds a reader.

## Consumer build.rs migration

Every hilavitkutin-* crate's build.rs calls
`mockspace::bootstrap::bootstrap_from_buildscript()`. Migrating to
also-call `hilavitkutin_build::bootstrap_from_buildscript()` is a
separate infra round that lands piecewise as each crate's
pragmas become observable.

## Windows MSVC toolchain support

DESIGN leans Linux + macOS. Windows MSVC needs its own flag-set
mapping for the three axes. Defer until a Windows consumer
surfaces.

## Apple Container workflow for macOS

DESIGN mentions `-Z llvm-plugins` is Linux-only; macOS uses
`-C passes=` or an Apple Container (Virtualization.framework,
<1s boot). The container-based workflow needs a trigger: when
the host is macOS + the pragma set requires an LLVM plugin,
hilavitkutin-build should be able to spawn an ARM Linux container
for the plugin pass. Defer until someone builds out the
orchestration.
